        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Buffeting winds swirl sharp grains of sand about the room.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"religon\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"38\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Religion</span> (expert) to state an Iroran koan about being complete only upon recognizing one&rsquo;s incompleteness, or <span data-pf2-check=\"occultism\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"41\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Occultism</span> (master) to create a ward against future hauntings</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 14
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt deactivates after 1 minute and re-forms after 1 hour. The haunt is disabled and doesn't re-form if at least two creatures spend 1 minute to create an image with the sand. Creating the image requires a successful <span data-pf2-skill-check=\"crafting\" data-pf2-label=\"Create Image in Sand DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"30\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Crafting</span> or <span data-pf2-skill-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-label=\"Create Image in Sand DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"30\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span>check.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) The haunt's violent winds savagely buffet everyone in the room, dealing [[/r 6d10+30 #bludgeoning damage]]{6d10+30 bludgeoning damage} to living creatures (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"34\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span>). On a critically failed save, a creature is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} for 1 minute.</p>"
